a COBOL program always contains 4 divisions.  
Identification Division: documentation purpose. 
Environment Division: used to specify file name and describe the specific computer equipments that will be used by the program  
Data Division: used to describe the input and output formats to be used by the program. also defines any constant and work areas necessary for the processing of datat
Procedure Division: contains the business logic. contains instructions necessary to read input and process it and create output as per your requirement.
